#. HTML: <section class="sutta" id="sn16.6"><article><div class="hgroup"><p class="division">
msgctxt "sn16.6:0.1"
msgid "Saṃyutta Nikāya 16 "
msgstr "Linked Discourses 16 "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "sn16.6:0.2"
msgid "1. Kassapavagga "
msgstr "1. Kassapa "

#. HTML: </p><h1>
msgctxt "sn16.6:0.3"
msgid "6. Ovādasutta "
msgstr "6. Advice "

#. HTML: </h1></div><p>
#. REF: pts-vp-pli2.204, sc1
msgctxt "sn16.6:1.1"
msgid "Rājagahe veḷuvane. "
msgstr "Near Rājagaha, in the Bamboo Grove. "

msgctxt "sn16.6:1.2"
msgid "Atha kho āyasmā mahākassapo yena bhagavā tenupasaṅkami; upasaṅkamitvā bhagavantaṃ abhivādetvā ekamantaṃ nisīdi. Ekamantaṃ nisinnaṃ kho āyasmantaṃ mahākassapaṃ bhagavā etadavoca: "
msgstr "Then Venerable Mahākassapa went up to the Buddha, bowed, and sat down to one side. The Buddha said to him: "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "sn16.6:1.3"
msgid "“ovada, kassapa, bhikkhū; "
msgstr "“Kassapa, advise the mendicants! "

msgctxt "sn16.6:1.4"
msgid "karohi, kassapa, bhikkhūnaṃ dhammiṃ kathaṃ. "
msgstr "Give them a Dhamma talk! "

msgctxt "sn16.6:1.5"
msgid "Ahaṃ vā, kassapa, bhikkhū ovadeyyaṃ tvaṃ vā; "
msgstr "Either you or I should advise the mendicants "

msgctxt "sn16.6:1.6"
msgid "ahaṃ vā bhikkhūnaṃ dhammiṃ kathaṃ kareyyaṃ tvaṃ vā”ti. "
msgstr "and give them a Dhamma talk.” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc2
msgctxt "sn16.6:2.1"
msgid "“Dubbacā kho, bhante, etarahi bhikkhū, dovacassakaraṇehi dhammehi samannāgatā, akkhamā, appadakkhiṇaggāhino anusāsaniṃ. "
msgstr "“Sir, the mendicants these days are hard to admonish, having qualities that make them hard to admonish. They’re impatient, and don’t take instruction respectfully. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. VAR: bhaṇḍañca → bhaṇḍuñca (bj)
#. VAR: abhijikañca → ābhiñjikañca (bj, pts1-2, mr) | ābhijjikañca (s1-3, km)
msgctxt "sn16.6:2.2"
msgid "Idhāhaṃ, bhante, addasaṃ bhaṇḍañca nāma bhikkhuṃ ānandassa saddhivihāriṃ abhijikañca nāma bhikkhuṃ anuruddhassa saddhivihāriṃ aññamaññaṃ sutena accāvadante: "
msgstr "Take the monk called Bhaṇḍa, Ānanda’s pupil. He’s been competing in studies with the monk called Abhiñjika, Anuruddha’s pupil. They say: "

msgctxt "sn16.6:2.3"
msgid "‘ehi, bhikkhu, ko bahutaraṃ bhāsissati, ko sundarataraṃ bhāsissati, ko cirataraṃ bhāsissatī’”ti. "
msgstr "‘Come on, monk, who can recite more? Who can recite better? Who can recite longer?’” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc3
msgctxt "sn16.6:3.1"
msgid "Atha kho bhagavā aññataraṃ bhikkhuṃ āmantesi: "
msgstr "So the Buddha said to a certain monk, "

msgctxt "sn16.6:3.2"
msgid "“ehi tvaṃ, bhikkhu, mama vacanena bhaṇḍañca bhikkhuṃ ānandassa saddhivihāriṃ abhijikañca bhikkhuṃ anuruddhassa saddhivihāriṃ āmantehi: "
msgstr "“Please, monk, in my name tell the monk called Bhaṇḍa, Ānanda’s pupil, and the monk called Abhiñjika, Anuruddha’s pupil that "

msgctxt "sn16.6:3.3"
msgid "‘satthā āyasmante āmantetī’”ti. "
msgstr "the teacher summons them.” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "sn16.6:3.4"
msgid "“Evaṃ, bhante”ti kho so bhikkhu bhagavato paṭissutvā yena te bhikkhū tenupasaṅkami; upasaṅkamitvā te bhikkhū etadavoca: "
msgstr "“Yes, sir,” that monk replied. He went to those monks and said, "

msgctxt "sn16.6:3.5"
msgid "“satthā āyasmante āmantetī”ti. "
msgstr "“Venerables, the teacher summons you.” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: pts-vp-pli2.205, sc4
msgctxt "sn16.6:4.1"
msgid "“Evamāvuso”ti kho te bhikkhū tassa bhikkhuno paṭissutvā yena bhagavā tenupasaṅkamiṃsu; upasaṅkamitvā bhagavantaṃ abhivādetvā ekamantaṃ nisīdiṃsu. Ekamantaṃ nisinne kho te bhikkhū bhagavā etadavoca: "
msgstr "“Yes, reverend,” those monks replied. They went to the Buddha, bowed, and sat down to one side. The Buddha said to them: "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "sn16.6:4.2"
msgid "“saccaṃ kira tumhe, bhikkhave, aññamaññaṃ sutena accāvadatha: "
msgstr "“Is it really true, monks, that you’ve been competing in studies, saying: "

msgctxt "sn16.6:4.3"
msgid "‘ehi, bhikkhu, ko bahutaraṃ bhāsissati, ko sundarataraṃ bhāsissati, ko cirataraṃ bhāsissatī’”ti? "
msgstr "‘Come on, monk, who can recite more? Who can recite better? Who can recite longer?’” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "sn16.6:4.4"
msgid "“Evaṃ, bhante”. "
msgstr "“Yes, sir.” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "sn16.6:4.5"
msgid "“Kiṃ nu kho me tumhe, bhikkhave, evaṃ dhammaṃ desitaṃ ājānātha: "
msgstr "“Have you ever known me to teach the Dhamma like this: "

msgctxt "sn16.6:4.6"
msgid "‘etha tumhe, bhikkhave, aññamaññaṃ sutena accāvadatha—"
msgstr "‘Please mendicants, compete in studies to "

msgctxt "sn16.6:4.7"
msgid "ehi, bhikkhu, ko bahutaraṃ bhāsissati, ko sundarataraṃ bhāsissati, ko cirataraṃ bhāsissatī’”ti? "
msgstr "see who can recite more and better and longer’?” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "sn16.6:4.8"
msgid "“No hetaṃ, bhante”. "
msgstr "“No, sir.” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "sn16.6:4.9"
msgid "“No ce kira me tumhe, bhikkhave, evaṃ dhammaṃ desitaṃ ājānātha, atha kiñcarahi tumhe, moghapurisā, kiṃ jānantā kiṃ passantā evaṃ svākkhāte dhammavinaye pabbajitā samānā aññamaññaṃ sutena accāvadatha: "
msgstr "“If you’ve never known me to teach the Dhamma like this, then what exactly do you know and see, you foolish men, that after going forth in such a well explained teaching and training you’d compete in studies to "

msgctxt "sn16.6:4.10"
msgid "‘ehi, bhikkhu, ko bahutaraṃ bhāsissati, ko sundarataraṃ bhāsissati, ko cirataraṃ bhāsissatī’”ti. "
msgstr "see who can recite more and better and longer?” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc5
msgctxt "sn16.6:5.1"
msgid "Atha kho te bhikkhū bhagavato pādesu sirasā nipatitvā bhagavantaṃ etadavocuṃ: "
msgstr "Then those monks bowed with their heads at the Buddha’s feet and said, "

#. VAR: yathābāle yathāmūḷhe yathāakusale → yathā bāle yathā mūḷhe yathā akusale (bj, pts1-2) | yathābālaṃ yathāmūḷhaṃ yathāakusalaṃ (?)
msgctxt "sn16.6:5.2"
msgid "“accayo no, bhante, accagamā, yathābāle yathāmūḷhe yathāakusale, ye mayaṃ evaṃ svākkhāte dhammavinaye pabbajitā samānā aññamaññaṃ sutena accāvadimha: "
msgstr "“We have made a mistake, sir. It was foolish, stupid, and unskillful of us in that after going forth in such a well explained teaching and training we competed in studies to "

msgctxt "sn16.6:5.3"
msgid "‘ehi, bhikkhu, ko bahutaraṃ bhāsissati, ko sundarataraṃ bhāsissati, ko cirataraṃ bhāsissatī’ti. "
msgstr "see who can recite more and better and longer. "

msgctxt "sn16.6:5.4"
msgid "Tesaṃ no, bhante, bhagavā accayaṃ accayato paṭiggaṇhātu āyatiṃ saṃvarāyā”ti. "
msgstr "Please, sir, accept our mistake for what it is, so we will restrain ourselves in future.” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc6
msgctxt "sn16.6:6.1"
msgid "“Taggha tumhe, bhikkhave, accayo accagamā yathābāle yathāmūḷhe yathāakusale, ye tumhe evaṃ svākkhāte dhammavinaye pabbajitā samānā aññamaññaṃ sutena accāvadittha: "
msgstr "“Indeed, monks, you made a mistake. It was foolish, stupid, and unskillful of you to act in that way. "

msgctxt "sn16.6:6.2"
msgid "‘ehi, bhikkhu, ko bahutaraṃ bhāsissati, ko sundarataraṃ bhāsissati, ko cirataraṃ bhāsissatī’ti. "
msgstr " "

#. VAR: taṃ vo mayaṃ → mayaṃ accayaṃ (bj, s1-3)
msgctxt "sn16.6:6.3"
msgid "Yato ca kho tumhe, bhikkhave, accayaṃ accayato disvā yathādhammaṃ paṭikarotha, taṃ vo mayaṃ paṭiggaṇhāma. "
msgstr "But since you have recognized your mistake for what it is, and have dealt with it properly, I accept it. "

msgctxt "sn16.6:6.4"
msgid "Vuddhi hesā, bhikkhave, ariyassa vinaye yo accayaṃ accayato disvā yathādhammaṃ paṭikaroti āyatiñca saṃvaraṃ āpajjatī”ti. "
msgstr "For it is growth in the training of the noble one to recognize a mistake for what it is, deal with it properly, and commit to restraint in the future.” "

#. HTML: </p><p class="endsection">
msgctxt "sn16.6:6.5"
msgid "Chaṭṭhaṃ. "
msgstr ""

